4. PoA Credential Schema — Canonical JSON Schema
==================================================

4.1 Schema-First Architecture
------------------------------

The PoA credential schema is the single source of truth for all GAuth credential formats. Both the JWT Extended Token (Section 5) and the W3C VC representation (Section 6) are projections of this schema.

4.2 Three-Layer Capability Model
---------------------------------

GiFo-RFC 0115 defines the Vollmacht (PoA) as a three-section document:

* Parties,
* Type & Scope,
* Requirements.

Within the scope, capabilities are organized into three layers:

::

  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │   PARTIES                                           │
  │   issuer, subject (agent), customer, project        │
  ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │   TYPE & SCOPE                                      │
  │                                                     │
  │   Layer 1: Core Verbs (Action Verbs)                │
  │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────┐     │
  │   │ foundry.file.create  │ foundry.file.modify│     │
  │   │ foundry.file.delete  │ foundry.dependency.add│  │
  │   │ foundry.command.run  │ foundry.agent.delegate│  │
  │   └───────────────────────────────────────────┘     │
  │                                                     │
  │   Layer 2: Permission-Based Capabilities            │
  │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────┐     │
  │   │ ToolPolicy per verb:                      │     │
  │   │      allowed: boolean                     │     │
  │   │      constraints: { pathPatterns, commands,│    │
  │   │            maxDelegationDepth, ... }       │     │
  │   └───────────────────────────────────────────┘     │
  │                                                     │
  │   Layer 3: Agent-Based Capabilities                 │
  │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────┐     │
  │   │ Platform Permissions:                     │     │
  │   │      deployment: { targets, auto_deploy } │     │
  │   │      database: { read, write, migrate }   │     │
  │   │      shell: { mode, allowlist/denylist }   │    │
  │   │      packages: { verified_only }          │     │
  │   │      external_apis: { allowed_domains }   │     │
  │   │      secrets: { read, create }            │     │
  │   └───────────────────────────────────────────┘     │
  ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │   REQUIREMENTS                                      │
  │   governance_profile, approval_mode, budget,        │
  │   session_limits, ttl                               │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

