4.4 Scope Checksum
-------------------

The ``scope_checksum`` claim in the JWT Extended Token provides tamper-evidence for the scope configuration. It is computed as:

::

  scope_checksum = SHA-256(
      canonical_json(scope.governance_profile, scope.phase,
                     scope.allowed_paths, scope.denied_paths,
                     scope.active_modules,
                     tool_permissions_hash,
                     platform_permissions_hash)
  )

Where ``canonical_json`` produces a deterministic JSON representation (sorted keys, no whitespace, UTF-8).

4.5 Permission Hashes
----------------------

Full permission objects (``core_verbs``, ``platform_permissions``) may be too large for the JWT size budget (Section 5.6). The JWT Extended Token carries hashes instead:

* ``tool_permissions_hash = SHA-256(canonical_json(core_verbs))``
* ``platform_permissions_hash = SHA-256(canonical_json(platform_permissions))``

Verifiers use stateful validation (Section 10.2.2) when they need the full permission set.

